Module interval_oop
Package interval_oop

Class Interval

java.lang.Object
interval_oop.Interval
public class Interval
extends java.lang.Object
Each instance of this class represents a sequence of consecutive integers. abstract state invariants: (a.k.a. public invariants)
Immutable
Any two calls of any zero-argument getter of this class on the same target object return equal values. (A getter is a method whose name starts with "get" or "is" followed by a capital letter.)
Invariants:
The width is nonnegative. 
getLowerBound() <= getUpperBound()

    • Interval

      public Interval​(int lowerBound, int upperBound)
      Initializes this object so that it represents the interval specified by the given lower and upper bound.
      Preconditions:
      The given lower bound is not greater than the given upper bound. 
      lowerBound <= upperBound
      Postconditions:
      This interval's lower bound equals the given lower bound. 
      getLowerBound() == lowerBound
      This interval's upper bound equals the given upper bound. 
      getUpperBound() == upperBound
